<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="328" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 181.9202/185:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Bandholtz</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate
                            Peace</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-13">October 13, 1919</date>.<lb/>[Received October
                                16—1:08 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>147. From Bandholtz for Polk. Reference your No. 76.<note n="55" xml:id="d328fn55"><hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi></note> Roumanians
                            have delivered 4,000 rifles and promised to deliver 6,000 more today. If
                            not delivered as promised will telegraph.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bandholtz</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>